


void setup()
//put your setup code here,to runs once:
{
pinMode(2,INPUT);
pinMode(13,OUTPUT);

}

void loop()
{
if(digitalRead(2)==LOW)
{
digitalWrite(13,HIGH);
}
else
{
digitalWrite(13,HIGH);
}
}


******************************************************** T  H  E O R Y ***********************************************************
ğŸ§  Explanation (Line by Line)
Line	Code	Explanation
1	void setup()	    This function runs only once when the Arduino starts. Used to set pin modes.
2	pinMode(2, INPUT);	   Configures digital pin 2 as an input (to read button state).
3	pinMode(13, OUTPUT);	  Configures digital pin 13 as an output (to control LED).
4	void loop()	   This function runs continuously after setup().
5	if (digitalRead(2) == LOW)	   Reads pin 2 â€” if button is pressed (LOW), run the next statement.
6	digitalWrite(13, HIGH);	  Turns ON the LED by setting pin 13 HIGH.
7	else	Otherwise (if button is not pressed)...
8	digitalWrite(13, LOW);	   Turns OFF the LED.

âš™ï¸**** Working Principle***

The button is connected to pin 2.

The LED is connected to pin 13.

When the button is pressed â†’ Arduino reads LOW on pin 2 â†’ LED turns ON.

When the button is released â†’ Arduino reads HIGH â†’ LED turns OFF.

This loop runs continuously.


